# 2. 旅立ち

Rui: ...
Rui: More...
Rui: Even more...
Rui: Even more captivating... Even more smile-inducing...
Rui: Those kinds of effects...
???: So, you should think really, really, really hard about this decision! For the sake of you now and you in the future, Rui!
???: Because I have a feeling that you won't be happy if you don't!
Rui: ...!
Rui: (What was I doing just now...?)
Rui: (This looks like... My directing notes?)
Rui: ...
Rui: I see... I thought I heard a voice just now...
Rui: But I must've fallen asleep writing down ideas for improvement again.
Rui: (I've grown a lot here at the Center Theatre... But I still have a long way to go as a director.)
Rui: (I don't have time to be napping.)
Rui: (What did I jot down last...? Ah, here. This must be it.)
Rui: (Right. I was working on an effect that involves moving around beneath the stage...)
Rui: (This is the scene where the protagonist faces off with the king and makes the decision to betray his country. So...)
Rui: (We could try capturing the audience's attention by using the lights in a clever way when he appears.)
Rui: It's a tragic scene, so it might be good to create a few moments where the faces of the characters on stage are darkened to the point where you can't see their expressions...
Rui: By switching between light and dark at the right tempo, we should be able to engage the audience's imaginations.
???: Rui.
Asahi: There you are. Are you still coming up with ideas...?
Rui: Asahi...? I thought you'd already gone home.
Asahi: I knew you'd forgotten. We've got a party scheduled after practice today, remember?
Rui: What party...?
Rui: Oh, of course.
ArcLand Cast Member A: Alright, now that the stars of tonight's party are here...
ArcLand Cast Member A: Let's wish Asahi and Kamishiro the best of luck when they go over to America's ArcLand! Cheers!
Everyone: Cheers!
ArcLand Cast Member B: Still, we weren't expecting you two to be late.
Rui: My apologies. I lost track of the time while coming up with ideas for improvement...
ArcLand Cast Member A: You really do spend every spare minute backstage coming up with ideas, don't you, Kamishiro?
Asahi: So true! When you're in director mode, you sometimes forget to eat and sleep. But...
Asahi: We've been asked to work over in the United States precisely because of your sheer dedication.
Rui: You think so...?
Rui: To be honest, I'm still having trouble processing all that. A part of me is wondering if I'm really the right choice.
ArcLand Cast Member C: Hehe. You did only join the Center Theatre a few months ago.
ArcLand Cast Member A: But even at the Center Theatre, you managed to become a hit director. You being scouted like this makes perfect sense to me.
Asahi: And the joint performance we did with the American ArcLand team pushed them to pick up the phone.
Asahi: It's no surprise they were impressed. I mean, you had the entire cast float in the air, and you created a giant waterfall using real water.
ArcLand Cast Member B: Yeah, those were so much fun!
ArcLand Cast Member B: I wasn't sure they'd be possible when you first suggested them... But we ended up really enjoying them while performing on stage!
Rui: Hehe. I'm glad to hear you say that.
Rui: That show was more or less the culmination of everything that I'd done until then.
Asahi: The culmination... Yeah, the ideas you came up with were on that level!
Asahi: And I'm looking forward to seeing what exciting ideas you come up with in the future.
ArcLand Cast Member B: Alright, this seems like a good time to hand you two your bouquets! Here you are!
Rui: Bouquets...?
Rui: Thank you very much. I wasn't expecting to be given such a nice send-off...
ArcLand Cast Member C: You're joking, right? There was no way we weren't going to celebrate our friends' talents being acknowledged.
Asahi: Haha. We really appreciate you saying that!
ArcLand Cast Member D: Hey, you two! The staff over here want to say hi!
ArcLand Cast Member B: Oh, you're being called over. Go on, you guys!
Asahi: How are you feeling...?
Rui: Huh?
Asahi: Your expression's been stiff for a little while now. You seem really anxious.
Asahi: I'm sorry if I'm mistaken, but if you're feeling overwhelmed...
Rui: Oh, no... I'm sorry for making you worry so much.
Rui: I'm actually fine. Though, I am feeling a little nervous.
Rui: After all, we'll be working as members of the Brillia Stage troupe during our time there. I hear that they're constantly looking for the best young actors and directors.
Rui: I'm wondering how I'll do as a director.
Rui: But...
Rui: I'm also looking forward to seeing what kinds of shows we get to do as a troupe...
Asahi: Think of it this way... With the two of us joining, the troupe is only going to become even more amazing!
Asahi: I believe that wherever we go, we can put on the greatest shows imaginable. So...
Asahi: Let's keep doing our best when we're in the US, Rui!
Rui: Asahi...
Rui: Yes. Many people look forward to seeing the Brillia Stage's performances since they're one of the best troupes in the world...
Rui: Just as we did when we made countless guests of the Center Theatre smile and laugh...
Rui: Let's put on more spectacular shows in the US.
Rui: (ArcLand has parks all around the world... But the shows they put on in the US stand head and shoulders above the rest...)
Rui: (I have no idea if my skills will actually get me anywhere. But...)
Rui: (To fulfill my dream of producing a show that transcends borders... I need to keep moving forward.)
Rui: (I need to make the absolute most of the kindness they showed me then.)
